<L>__{126. on the gun deck night}
<A>__{mowett watches the second hand of his stopwatch, glancing up as he notes the concentrated fury of the men swabbing, ramming, heaving in, heaving out, firing at a raft this time. and he stops the watch as the first gun fires.}
<C>__{mowett}
<D>__{one minute forty nine, sir!}
<A>__{his voice is drowned by the firing of the other guns in close succession entirely demolishing the raft, the sound mixing with cheering and the frenzied hammering of nagel and his mates as the gun deck partitions are cheerfully re erected.}
